{
  "texts": [
    "However, despite the growing body of research, these areas remain underexplored, especially in translating theoretical models into actionable classroom practices (Yu and Liu, 2021).",
    "Comprehensive research on developing and evaluating STEM textbooks is lacking (Yu and Yang, 2022).",
    "Additionally, there is a need for diverse perspectives to be incorporated into empirical research to broaden its scope and applicability (Meng et al. 2022; Zhong et al. 2022).",
    "Ma (2021) explored the evolving landscape of STEM education in China, advocating a shift from a policy-driven, economically focused framework to a more holistic and experiential approach.",
    "This shift underscores the importance of integrating STEM learning with real-world experiences, ethics, and historical contexts, which are crucial for creating an education system that is both informative and transformative."
  ]
}